:::summary
Ethics is the branch of philosophy that investigates morality — what is right and wrong, good and bad, what we owe to each other, and how we should live. The three dominant Western ethical theories — virtue ethics, deontology, and utilitarianism — each illuminate a different dimension of moral life. Ethics is not merely an academic exercise; it is the disciplined pursuit of wisdom about how to live well and treat others rightly.
